Guided cycling tour is a relatively fresh concept in Ladakh. It is an unconventional platform that diligently stresses on contesting the experience side of travelling.
Cycling trips convey the pure essence of attaining a broader perception of the region,  while constraining the disruption of the eco system to its minimum. These trips conduct a direct impact on promoting sustainable tourism, and further develop an eco friendly sphere.
Explore the most removed of places and gain a diverse perspective of #ladakh, both physically as well as culturally.

JUNE, establishes the initiation trips of #unexploredladakh 
FROM 3rd to 7th,
Trip starts from LEH to the village of Mangu, attaining around 106 kilometers of sheer cycling.

And.. An additional trip that is incomparably different to our normal quests 
FROM 10th to 13th JUNE,

This trip revolves at night when the moon is at its brightest. The idea of this trip is to take the utmost advantage of the natural setting, and gain a unique perspective.

SO PUT YOUR CYCLING SHOES ON AND EXPLORE THIS MAJESTIC PLACE CALLED LADAKH ON A PAIR OF WHEELS.

#donkeysanctuary #unexploredladakh #hippieinhills

Have you ever wondered why the hammerhead shark looks the way that it does?? 🔨 
The unique shape of the hammerhead shark’s head gives it excellent vision 👀 It can use both eyes together to see complete images. It even has 360-degree vision, which means it can see above, below, in front and behind it at all times! 😱How cool is that! This makes the hammerhead shark’s vision better than other sharks 🦈 // photo by Artie Kopelman #hammertime #funfacts #adventure #experience #share #advocate #sharklivesmatter #oceanminded #oceansneedsharks #finsup #respectlife #respectthefin

MAGER @IPIENKHOUSE

Tinggal di @ipienkhouse Yogyakarta bikin aku susah move on, suasana penginapan yang luxury dengan teman teman yang semuanya ramah dan siap membantu kapanpun aku perlu. Makanan yang disajikanpun mulai dari sarapan, makan siang sampai malam bikin celana jeans aku makin ketat alias harus lepas kancing hehe.

Apalagi kalau sudah ngomongin masalah kamar, pengen nya mager aja githu di dalam. Mulai dari cuma malas2 an di atas ranjang, sampai duduk di sofa sambil baca buku atau kadang aku buka korden kamar dan langsung bisa melihat kolam renang dari balik kaca di samping tempat duduk aku.

Sayangnya aku harus balik Bandung lagi dan pastinya aku akan menuliskan pengalaman aku selama tinggal di @ipienkhouse di blog aku nantinya, supaya kalian bisa lebih detail melihat apa saja yang ada di dalam Ipienk House Beyond Luxury ini. Oiya buat semuanya kalau pengen informasi tentang @ipienkhouse jangan malu malu buat tulis di Comment ya.
